\subsection{DIVE SPAWN FRAMEWORK}

Underwater dive surveys using SCUBA gear
were instituted in \Sexpr{pars$years$dive} and follow
a two-stage systematic sampling design where
transects are the first sampling stage, and
individual quadrats within transects
are the second sampling stage \citep{Jessen1978}.
First we describe the understory spawn framework,
then we describe the Macrocystis spawn framework
which is related to understory, but simpler.

\subsubsection{UNDERSTORY SPAWN FRAMEWORK}

Two steps are required to calculate mean understory egg density
in each surveyed spawn $s$ (\autoref{tabNotationIndices}).
First, mean egg density for transect $t$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqStatRhoT}
\mean{\rho}_{txsnry} =
\frac{1}{Q_{txsnry}} \sum_{q=1}^{Q_{txsnry}} \rho_{qtxsnry},
\end{equation}
where $Q_{txsnry}$ is the number of quadrats,
$\rho_{qtxsnry}$ is egg density in thousands of eggs per square metre
($10^3 \cdot \text{eggs} \cdot \text{m}^{-2}$; \autoref{tabNotationStat}), and
$\mean{\rho}_{txsnry}$ is in $10^3 \cdot \text{eggs} \cdot \text{m}^{-2}$.
Throughout this report,
`$\mean{\phantom{x}}$' indicates the mean of the variable that it covers
(e.g., $\mean{\rho}$ is the mean of $\rho$ in \autoref{eqStatRhoT}).
Note that we report eggs in thousands (i.e., $10^3 \cdot \text{eggs}$)
in this document and in the \textbf{R} package (\autoref{secPack}).
Before we calculate mean egg density for spawn $s$,
we determine the mean number of potential quadrats
for survey type $x$ in spawn $s$
\begin{equation}\label{eqStatQSPrime}
\mean{Q}_{xsnry}' =
\frac{1}{T_{xsnry}} \sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}} Q_{txsnry}',
\end{equation}
where $T_{xsnry}$ is the number of transects,
$Q_{txsnry}'$ is the number of potential quadrats
(i.e., based on spawn width), and
$\mean{Q}_{xsnry}'$ is in number of quadrats.
Then, we calculate mean egg density in eggs per square metre
for survey type $x$ in spawn $s$
\begin{equation}\label{eqStatRhoS}
\mean{\rho}_{xsnry} =
\frac{1}{T_{xsnry} \mean{Q}_{xsnry}'}
\sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}} Q_{txsnry}' \mean{\rho}_{txsnry},
\end{equation}
where $T_{xsnry}$ is the number of transects,
$\mean{Q}_{xsnry}'$ is the mean number of potential quadrats
from \autoref{eqStatQSPrime},
$Q_{txsnry}'$ is the number of potential quadrats,
$\mean{\rho}_{txsnry}$ is the mean transect egg density from \autoref{eqStatRhoT}, and
$\mean{\rho}_{xsnry}$ is in $10^3 \cdot \text{eggs} \cdot \text{m}^{-2}$.
The egg density estimator from \autoref{eqStatRhoS} is unbiased,
and the variance is
\begin{multline}\label{eqStatSigmaS}
\sigma_{xsnry}^2 =
\frac{T_{xsnry}'-T_{xsnry}}{T_{xsnry}T_{xsnry}'} \sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}}
\frac{\left(Q_{txsnry}'\mean{\rho}_{txsnry}
-\mean{Q}_{xsnry}'\mean{\rho}_{xsnry}\right)^2}
{\mean{Q}_{xsnry}'^2\left(T_{xsnry}-1\right)} \\
+ \frac{f_{xsnry}'}{T_{xsnry}^2} \sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}}
\left(\frac{Q_{txsnry}'}{\mean{Q}_{snry}'}\right)^2
\frac{\left(1-f_{txsnry}''\right)\sigma_{txsnry}^2}{Q_{txsnry}},
\end{multline}
where $T_{xsnry}'$ is the number of potential transects
(i.e., based on spawn length),
$T_{xsnry}$ is the number of transects,
$Q_{txsnry}'$ is the number of potential quadrats,
$\mean{\rho}_{txsnry}$ is the mean egg density from \autoref{eqStatRhoT},
$\mean{Q}_{xsnry}'$ is the mean number of potential quadrats
from \autoref{eqStatQSPrime},
$\mean{\rho}_{xsnry}$ is the mean spawn egg density from \autoref{eqStatRhoS},
$f_{xsnry}'$ is the transect sampling fraction for
survey type $x$ in spawn $s$
\begin{equation}\label{eqFT}
f_{xsnry}' = \frac{T_{xsnry}}{T_{xsnry}'},
\end{equation}
$f_{txsnry}''$ is the quadrat sampling fraction for transect $t$
\begin{equation}\label{eqFQ}
f_{txsnry}'' = \frac{Q_{txsnry}}{Q_{txsnry}'},
\end{equation}
where $Q_{txsnry}$ is the number of quadrats, and
$\sigma_{txsnry}^2$ is the within transect egg density variance
\begin{equation}\label{eqStatSigmaT}
\sigma_{txsnry}^2 =
\frac{1}{{Q_{txsnry} - 1}}
\sum_{q=1}^{Q_{txsnry}}
\left(\rho_{qtxsnry} - \mean{\rho}_{txsnry}\right)^2,
\end{equation}
where $\rho_{qtxsnry}$ is egg density, and
$\sigma_{txsnry}^2$ is in units of $\rho^2$.

