\subsection{PLANT OBSERVATIONS}\label{secMacroP}

For each mature plant $p$ (step \ref{mPlant} in \autoref{figFlow}),
surveyors count the number of stalks $K_{ptxsnry}$.

\subsection{TRANSECT OBSERVATIONS AND CALCULATIONS}\label{secMacroT}

At the transect $t$ level (step \ref{mTrans} in \autoref{figFlow}),
spawn width is $W_{txsnry}$, and
transect swath is $\chi_{txsnry} = 2\,\text{m}$, both in metres.
We calculate the area in transect $t$ as
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroAreaTS}
A_{txsnry} = W_{txsnry} \chi_{txsnry}
\end{equation}
where $W_{txsnry}$ is spawn width in metres,
$\chi_{txsnry}$ is transect swath in metres, and
$A_{txsnry}$ is in square metres.
In addition, divers estimate summary statistics for
mature Macrocystis plants $p$ along transect $t$:
mean height $\mean{H}_{txsnry}$ in metres and
mean number of egg layers $\mean{E}_{txsnry}$.
We calculate the total number of stalks $K$ in transect $t$ as
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroStalksTS}
K_{txsnry} = \sum_{p=1}^{P_{txsnry}} K_{ptxsnry},
\end{equation}
where $K_{ptxsnry}$ is the number of stalks and
$K_{txsnry}$ is in number of stalks.

\subsection{SPAWN OBSERVATIONS AND CALCULATIONS}\label{secMacroS}

At the spawn $s$ level (step \ref{mSpawn} in \autoref{figFlow}),
the Macrocystis bed length is $L_{xsnry}'$ in metres.
If $L_{xsnry}'$ is inadvertently not recorded,
we set $L_{xsnry}'$ to the spawn length $L_{xsnry}$.
The mean width for survey type $x$ in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroWidthS}
\mean{W}_{xsnry} = \frac{1}{T_{xsnry}} \sum_{t=1}^{Txsnry} W_{txsnry},
\end{equation}
where $T_{xsnry}$ is the number of transects,
$W_{txsnry}$ is the spawn width, and
$\mean{W}_{xsnry}$ is in metres.
The total area of transects for survey type $x$ in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroAreaS}
A_{xsnry} = \sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}} A_{txsnry},
\end{equation}
where $A_{txsnry}$ is the transect area from \autoref{eqMacroAreaTS},
and $A_{xsnry}$ is in square metres.

Three metrics are required to calculate
the number of eggs on Macrocystis plants \citep{HaegeleSchweigert1990}:
number of egg layers,
plant height, and
number of stalks per plant.
First, the mean number of egg layers
for survey type $x$ in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroLayersS}
\mean{E}_{xsnry} = \frac{1}{T_{xsnry}} \sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}} \mean{E}_{txsnry},
\end{equation}
where $T_{xsnry}$ is the number of transects in spawn $s$,
$\mean{E}_{txsnry}$ is the mean number of egg layers $t$, and
$\mean{E}_{xsnry}$ is in number of egg layers.
Second, the mean plant height in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroHeightS}
\mean{H}_{xsnry} = \frac{1}{T_{xsnry}} \sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}} \mean{H}_{txsnry},
\end{equation}
where $T_{xsnry}$ is the number of transects,
$\mean{H}_{txsnry}$ is the mean plant height, and
$\mean{H}_{xsnry}$ is in metres.
The third metric is the number of stalks per plant,
which we calculate in three steps.
The total number of observed stalks
for survey type $x$ in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroStalksS}
K_{xsnry} = \sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}} K_{txsnry},
\end{equation}
where $K_{txsnry}$ is the number of stalks from \autoref{eqMacroStalksTS} and
$K_{xsnry}$ is in number of stalks.
The total number of observed plants
for survey type $x$ in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroPlantsS}
P_{xsnry} = \sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}} P_{txsnry},
\end{equation}
where $P_{txsnry}$ is the number of plants and
$P_{xsnry}$ is in number of plants.
Thus, the mean number of stalks per plant
for survey type $x$ in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroStalksPerPlantS}
\mean{\kappa}_{xsnry} = \frac{K_{xsnry}}{P_{xsnry}},
\end{equation}
where $K_{xsnry}$ is the number of stalks from \autoref{eqMacroStalksS},
$P_{xsnry}$ is the number of plants from \autoref{eqMacroPlantsS}, and
$\mean{\kappa}_{xsnry}$ is in number of stalks per plant.

\citet{HaegeleSchweigert1990} developed a model of the number of eggs per plant
as a function of the three aforementioned metrics
(number of egg layers, plant height, and number of stalks per plant)
using a nonlinear multiple regression model
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroEggsPerPlantS}
\mean{\psi}_{xsnry} =
\xi \mean{E}_{xsnry}^\gamma
\mean{H}_{xsnry}^\delta
\mean{\kappa}_{xsnry}^\epsilon
10^3,
\end{equation}
where $\xi$ is the regression slope,
$\mean{E}_{xsnry}$ is the mean number of egg layers
from \autoref{eqMacroLayersS},
$\gamma$ is the regression exponent on $\mean{E}_{xsnry}$,
$\mean{H}_{xsnry}$ is the mean plant height from \autoref{eqMacroHeightS},
$\delta$ is the regression exponent on $\mean{H}_{xsnry}$,
$\mean{\kappa}_{xsnry}$ is the mean number of stalks per plant
from \autoref{eqMacroStalksPerPlantS},
$\epsilon$ is the regression exponent on $\mean{\kappa}_{xsnry}$, and
$\mean{\psi}_{xsnry}$ is in $\text{eggs} \cdot 10^3 \cdot \text{plant}^{-1}$
(\autoref{figMacroEggsPerPlantS}).
Mean Macrocystis egg density in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroDensS}
\mean{\rho}_{xsnry} = \frac{\mean{\psi}_{xsnry} P_{xsnry}}{A_{xsnry}},
\end{equation}
where
$\mean{\psi}_{xsnry}$ is the mean number of eggs per plant
from \autoref{eqMacroEggsPerPlantS},
$P_{xsnry}$ is the number of plants from \autoref{eqMacroPlantsS},
$A_{xsnry}$ is the total area of transects from \autoref{eqMacroAreaS}, and
$\mean{\rho}_{xsnry}$ is in $10^3 \cdot \text{eggs} \cdot \text{m}^{-2}$.

The Macrocystis spawn index in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqMacroIndS}
B_{xsnry}' = \frac{\mean{\rho}_{xsnry} L_{xsnry}' \mean{W}_{xsnry} 10^3} {\theta},
\end{equation}
where $\mean{\rho}_{xsnry}$ is the mean egg density from \autoref{eqMacroDensS},
$L_{xsnry}'$ is the Macrocystis bed length,
$\mean{W}_{xsnry}$ is the mean spawn width from \autoref{eqMacroWidthS},
$\theta$ is the egg conversion factor from \autoref{eqECF}, and
$B_{xsnry}'$ is in tonnes (step \ref{mInd} in \autoref{figFlow}).

