\subsection{QUADRAT OBSERVATIONS AND CALCULATIONS}\label{secUnderQ}

We calculate two separate estimates of egg density at the quadrat level
(step \ref{uQuad} in \autoref{figFlow}):
spawn on substrate $i'$ and spawn on algae $v$.
\citet{HaegeleEtal1979} developed a model of substrate $i'$ egg density
from egg layers using a linear model
\begin{equation}\label{eqUnderDensSubQTS}
\rho_{i'qtxsnry} = \varphi E_{i'qtxsnry} \phi_{i'qtxsnry},
\end{equation}
where $\varphi$ is the regression slope,
$E_{i'qtxsnry}$ is the number of egg layers,
$\phi_{i'qtxsnry}$ is the proportion of substrate covered by spawn, and
$\rho_{i'qtxsnry}$ is substrate egg density
in $10^3 \cdot \text{eggs} \cdot \text{m}^{-2}$ (\autoref{figUnderDensSubQTS}).

