The total understory egg density for quadrat $q$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqUnderDensQTS}
\rho_{qtxsnry} = \rho_{i'qtxsnry} + \sum_{v=1}^{V_{qtxsnry}} \rho_{vqtxsnry},
\end{equation}
where $\rho_{i'qtxsnry}$ is substrate egg density
from \autoref{eqUnderDensSubQTS},
$\rho_{vqtxsnry}$ is algae egg density from \autoref{eqUnderDensAlgVQTS}, and
$\rho_{qtxsnry}$ is in $10^3 \cdot \text{eggs} \cdot \text{m}^{-2}$.
Thus, we assume that eggs on substrate and algae are independent,
and can be combined.

\subsection{TRANSECT OBSERVATIONS AND CALCULATIONS}\label{secUnderT}

At the transect level (step \ref{uTrans} in \autoref{figFlow}),
the mean understory egg density in transect $t$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqUnderDensTS}
\mean{\rho}_{txsnry} =
\frac{1}{Q_{txsnry}} \sum_{q=1}^{Q_{txsnry}} \rho_{qtxsnry},
\end{equation}
where $Q_{txsnry}$ is the number of quadrats,
$\rho_{qtxsnry}$ is total understory egg density
from \autoref{eqUnderDensQTS}, and
$\mean{\rho}_{txsnry}$ is in $10^3 \cdot \text{eggs} \cdot \text{m}^{-2}$.
Note that we update spawn width to correct for errors regarding
the assumed accuracy of transect lines used to measure spawn width for
understory surveys between \Sexpr{min(under_width_facs$Year)} and
\Sexpr{max(under_width_facs$Year)} (\autoref{secWidthUnder}).

\subsection{SPAWN OBSERVATIONS AND CALCULATIONS}\label{secUnderS}

At the spawn level (step \ref{uSpawn} in \autoref{figFlow}),
the mean width of survey type $x$ in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqUnderWidthMuS}
\mean{W}_{xsnry} = \frac{1}{T_{xsnry}} \sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}} W_{txsnry},
\end{equation}
where $T_{xsnry}$ is the number of transects,
$W_{txsnry}$ is the spawn width, and
$\mean{W}_{xsnry}$ is in metres.
The algae bed length is $L_{xsnry}''$, also in metres.
As with Macrocystis spawn calculations,
if $L_{xsnry}''$ is inadvertently not recorded,
we set $L_{xsnry}''$ to the spawn length $L_{xsnry}$.
Thus, we assume that eggs on substrate and eggs on algae
are represented by the same length measurement.

Next, we calculate the weighted mean egg density in spawn $s$, where
transect egg density is weighted by spawn width at transect $t$, $W_{txsnry}$.
We calculate a weighted mean because spawn width varies along the spawn length;
a weighted mean ensures that transects contribute proportionally to their area.
The mean egg density for survey type $x$ in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqUnderDensMuS}
\mean{\rho}_{xsnry} =
\frac{\sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}} \mean{\rho}_{txsnry} W_{txsnry}}
{\sum_{t=1}^{T_{xsnry}} W_{txsnry}},
\end{equation}
where $\mean{\rho}_{txsnry}$ is the mean understory egg density
from \autoref{eqUnderDensTS},
$W_{txsnry}$ is the spawn width, and
$\mean{\rho}_{xsnry}$ is in $10^3 \cdot \text{eggs} \cdot \text{m}^{-2}$.

The understory spawn index in spawn $s$ is
\begin{equation}\label{eqUnderIndS}
B_{xsnry}' = \frac{\mean{\rho}_{xsnry} L_{xsnry}'' \mean{W}_{xsnry} 10^3} {\theta},
\end{equation}
where $\mean{\rho}_{xsnry}$ is the mean understory egg density
from \autoref{eqUnderDensMuS},
$L_{xsnry}''$ is the algae bed length,
$\mean{W}_{xsnry}$ is the mean spawn width from \autoref{eqUnderWidthMuS},
$\theta$ is the egg conversion factor from \autoref{eqECF}, and
$B_{xsnry}'$ is in tonnes (step \ref{uInd} in \autoref{figFlow}).

\section{TOTAL SPAWN CALCULATIONS}\label{secTotal}

This section describes step \ref{tIndex} in \autoref{figFlow}.
Recall that spawn index calculations
have a nested hierarchical structure
(e.g., substrate type $i$ is nested within sample $j$
for surface spawn calculations in \autoref{secSurf}).
However, quantities at the survey type $x$ in spawn $s$ level
are not necessarily nested and hierarchical.
For example, $B_{xsnry}'$ is the finest scale
that we calculate the spawn index (\autoref{secProt}),
which we could aggregate by any combination of
survey type $x$, spawn $s$, location $n$, region $r$, and year $y$.
To prevent confusion,
we use the notation of \cite{Montgomery2012} in the following calculations,
where `$\cdot$' subscript notation indicates summation
over the subscript that it replaces.

First we sum over survey type $x$ to calculate
the total spawn index in spawn $s$
(\autoref{tabNotationIndices} and \autoref{tabNotationTotal})
\begin{equation}\label{eqTotIndSLRY}
B_{\cdot snry}' = \sum_{x=1}^{X_{snry}} B_{xsnry}',
\end{equation}
where $B_{xsnry}'$ is the spawn index for
surface, Macrocystis, and understory spawn survey types from
\autoref{eqSurfIndS}, \autoref{eqMacroIndS}, and \autoref{eqUnderIndS},
respectively and
$B_{\cdot snry}'$ is in tonnes (step \ref{tIndex} in \autoref{figFlow}).

